<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/189: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commanding General of the American Expeditionary
                                Forces in Siberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GMGWS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Graves</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                The Adjutant General</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HPC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harris</hi></persName>)<note n="71" xml:id="d564fn71">Copy transmitted to the Acting Secretary of State
                                Sept. 29.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-28"><hi rend="italic">September 28,
                                    1919</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>483. <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> representatives here
                            will take over rifles with understanding that none will be delivered to
                            any of <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>’s military
                            representatives east of Irkutsk. I will send troops with rifles at least
                            as far as Verkhnie Udinsk to see that none of these arms fall into the
                            hands of bands now dominating situation east of Lake Baikal.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_GMGWS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Graves</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>